The UNITED STATES of America v. Frances WINSTEL. No. 8740. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Jan. 7, 1937. Ben Harrison, U. S. Atty., of Los Angeles, Cal. W. W. Wallace, of Los Angeles, Cal., for appellee.

Before GARRECHT, MATHEWS, and HANEY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon stipulation of counsel for respective parties, and good cause therefor appearing, ordered appeal herein dismissed, that a judgment of dismissal be filed and entered accordingly, and the mandate of this court issued forthwith.
